study_pop.textblock:
Patients with autoimmune liver disease: All enrolled autoimmune liver diseases meet the
diagnostic criteria of China's Consensus on Diagnosis and Treatment of Autoimmune Liver
Disease (2015);

criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  1) Patients with autoimmune liver disease: All enrolled autoimmune liver diseases meet
             the diagnostic criteria of China's Consensus on Diagnosis and Treatment of Autoimmune
             Liver Disease (2015);

          -  2) no hormones and / or immunosuppressants and other liver protection drugs;

          -  3) Sign the written informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  1) Combine other hepatitis virus (HCV, HDV) infections;

          -  2) viral liver disease;

          -  3) HIV infection;

          -  4) long-term alcohol abuse and / or other liver damage drugs;

          -  5) mental illness;

          -  6) Evidence of liver tumors (liver cancer or AFP > 100 ng/ml);

          -  7) decompensated cirrhosis;

          -  8) Serious diseases such as heart, brain, lung, kidney, etc. can not participate in
             long-term follow-up;

          -  9) There are hormones and / or immunosuppressants and other liver protection drugs.
